OAuth Configuration (Google Example)
========================================================================================================================
click the below link
üëâ https://console.cloud.google.com

Go to Select Project ---> New Project --> Name (spring-oauth-google) ---> create

Go to API & Services ---> OAuth consent screen
Click on Get Started
Project Name :
name
email
Audience :
External
Contact Information :
developer email id

agree
create

Go to
APIs & Services ‚Üí Credentials
Application Type -> Web Application
Authorized Redirect URI -> http://localhost:8080/login/oauth2/code/google
create
client-id
client-secret-id
========================================================================================================================
Application yml file configuration
========================================================================================================================
spring:
  security:
    oauth2:
      client:
        registration:
          google:
            client-id: YOUR_CLIENT_ID
            client-secret: YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET
            scope:
              - email
              - profile
========================================================================================================================
Scope	                      What you get
email	                    User‚Äôs email address + verified flag
profile	                    Name, profile picture, Google ID
========================================================================================================================
How to set environmental value like password
========================================================================================================================
‚úÖ OPTION 1: Set environment variable in OS (BEST PRACTICE)
üîπ Windows (PowerShell)
setx DB_PASSWORD "your_postgres_password"
üëâ Close & reopen IDE / terminal after this.
üîπ Linux / macOS
export DB_PASSWORD=your_postgres_password
üîπ Verify it is set
echo $DB_PASSWORD       # Linux / macOS
echo %DB_PASSWORD%     # Windows cmd
========================================================================================================================
‚úÖ OPTION 2: IntelliJ / Eclipse Run Configuration (Most Common)
IntelliJ IDEA
Run ‚Üí Edit Configurations
Select your Spring Boot app
Environment variables
Add:
DB_PASSWORD=your_postgres_password
Apply ‚Üí Run
========================================================================================================================
‚úÖ OPTION 3: .env file (Clean & safe)
Create .env
DB_PASSWORD=your_postgres_password
Add .env to .gitignore
.env
Add dependency (optional but nice if you add)
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.github.cdimascio</groupId>
  <artifactId>dotenv-java</artifactId>
  <version>3.0.0</version>
</dependency>
========================================================================================================================
‚úÖ OPTION 4: Default value (NOT for prod)
password: ${DB_PASSWORD:postgres}
If env variable missing ‚Üí uses postgres.
========================================================================================================================